README
CDH keeps server configurations under /var/run/cloudera-scm-agent/process, instead of /etc/${HADOOP_COMPONENT, e.g. hive}/conf.
The exist configuration locations only contain client configuration.

 

Notes
CM databases
-------------------------------------------------------
Navigator: /etc/cloudera-scm-server/db.mgmt.properties
CM: /etc/cloudera-scm-server/db.properties

Configuration
-------------------------------------------------------
Client: /etc/$HADOOP_COMPONENT, e.g. hive, hadoop, etc.
Server:  /var/run/cloudera-scm-agent/process
DB passwords are encrypted.
Hive conf: 781-hive-HIVEMETASTORE/hive-site.xml
<name>javax.jdo.option.ConnectionUserName</name>
<value>hive</value>
<name>javax.jdo.option.ConnectionPassword</name>
<value>********</value>
Oozie conf: 1309-oozie-OOZIE_SERVER/oozie-site.xml (latest directory)
<name>oozie.service.JPAService.jdbc.username</name>
<value>oozie</value>
<name>oozie.service.JPAService.jdbc.password</name>
<value>********</value>
